The paper focuses on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) research. The use of capsules, a concept introduced by Geoffrey Hinton, is a key aspect of the proposed method, which falls under the category of deep learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of adaptive gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research.
